Data Profiling Summary¶

The issues in the dataframe are as follows:¶

  1. In intial dataset, there were 104910 rows and 16 columns in our dataset.
  1. We created different dataframe 'df_Business' which contain 50000 rows and 16 columns.
  1. These columns contain integer, float and categorical values.
  1. Cleanliness, baggage handling, inflight entertainment, food and drink, inflight wifi service are all telling us rating which should be integer, but given in float format. Departure/arrival time convenient and age should ideally be integer, but values are in float format.
  1. We also observed unique values in each column.
  1. Column Class has single value. This column is not giving us any information. Hence, we may consider to eliminate them.
  1. There is format error in column values of all columns except Flight Distance,Departure Delay in minutes.
  1. There are missing values in all the columns.
  1. We have 3064 duplicate rows.

Handle missing values¶

Syntax:

DataFrame.dropna(axis=0, how='any', inplace=False)¶

Arguments:

axis: Default – 0¶
  • 0, or index : Drop rows which contain NaN values.
  • 1, or columns : Drop columns which contain NaN value.
how: Default – ‘any’¶
  • any : Drop rows / columns which contain any NaN values.
  • all : Drop rows / columns which contain all NaN values.
inplace (bool): Default- False¶
  • If True, modifies the calling dataframe object

Annotations¶

Here's a summary of the key points for each column in the Data Frame:

1. Gender:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object," which often contains mixed data types
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Had various values, including "Male," "Female," "F," "M," "Fe Male,"and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to three categories: "Male," "Female," and "Unknown."
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 1761 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with "Unknown".

2. Customer Type:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it was of data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like "Loyal Customer," "Disloyal Customer," "disloyal," and "Loyal."
  • Unique Values After: Simplified into three categories: "Loyal Customer," "Disloyal Customer," and "Unknown."
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 1761 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with "Unknown".

3. Age:¶

  • Data Type Before: Originally a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Had 75 unique values.
  • Unique Values After: The number of unique values changed to 73 because we changed 0 and 'nan' to the mean value(42).
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 2627 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mean of the column.

4. Type of Travel:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like 'Personal Travel' 'Business travel' 'Business' nan.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified into three categories: "Personal Travel," "Business Travel," and "Unknown."
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 1761 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with "Unknown".

5. Class:¶

  • Data Type Before: Originally an "object."
  • Data Type After: Removed from the dataset.

6. Flight Distance:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Had 3575 unique values.
  • Unique Values After: Changed to 3573 becuase we changed its negative and missing value to the mode of the column.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 3396 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled were replaced by the mode of the column.

7. Inflight wifi service:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Included values like 3. 1. 2. 4. 0. 5. and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 3, 1, 2, 4, 5. We have replaced 0 with least values 1.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 1761 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

8. Departure/Arrival time convenient:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Included values like 2. 1. 4. 0. 5. 3. and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers from 2, 1, 4, 5, 3. We have replaced 0 with least values 1.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 1761 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

9. Ease of Online booking:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like "3," "4," "0," "5,","2","1" and "Unknown" and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 3, 4, 1, 5, 2. We have replaced 0 with least values 1.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 7295 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

10. Food and drink:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like "5," "4," "1," "3," "Great," and "0."
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 5, 4, 1, 3, 2 , changed Great to 5 and We have replaced 0 with least values 1 and missing values with its mode.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 7295 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

11. Inflight entertainment:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Included values like 1. 2. 3. 4. 5. 10. 0. and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 1, 4, 2, 3, 5 and we replaced 0 with least values 1 and 10 with the greatest value 5.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 6351 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

12. Baggage handling:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like "1," "2," "3," "5," and "A." and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 1, 4, 2, 3, 5. Here we have replaced A with 5 considering grades.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 6351 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

13. Cleanliness:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Included values like 3.0, 4.0, 2.0,5.0 and missing values.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to integers 3, 4, 2, 5, 1.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 6351 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handledby replacing them with the mode of the column.

14. Departure Delay in Minutes:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially a float.
  • Data Type After: Transformed to int for whole numbers.
  • Unique Values Before: Had 359 unique values.
  • Unique Values After: The number of unique values after is 357. So if we would have change the negative values to their respective positive vlaues, that would mean that the flight is delayed which is not the case. Hence, all negative values are changed to 0 since it doesn't make any sense for the flight to leave earlier than expected.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 6351 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

15. Arrival Delay in Minutes:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Had 364 unique values.
  • Unique Values After: Reduced to 361 unique values. We observed that there are few values like'Three','9..' which were changed to '3','9'.
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 7902 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with the mode of the column.

16. Satisfaction:¶

  • Data Type Before: Initially, it had the data type "object."
  • Data Type After: Transformed to "string" for consistency.
  • Unique Values Before: Included variations like 'Dissatisfied' 'neutral' 'satisfied' 'dissatisfied' nan '0' '1'.
  • Unique Values After: Simplified to "Dissatisfied," "Neutral," "Satisfied," and "Unknown."
  • No. Of Missing Values Before: Had 2160 missing values.
  • No. Of Missing Values After: All missing values were handled by replacing them with "Unknown".
